-- MF Global Trustee Says He’ll Allow All or Part of 12,143 Claims for Losses
-- B y   L i n d a   S a n d l e r
-- 2012-03-02T23:28:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-02/mf-global-trustee-says-he-ll-allow-all-or-part-of-12-143-claims-for-losses.html
The trustee liquidating the MF
Global Inc. brokerage, who is halfway through assessing
commodity customers’ claims filed by Jan. 31, said he has
allowed all or part of 12,143 claims filed while denying three.  After more analysis, he plans to distribute unspecified
amounts to claimholders, he said today in a filing in U.S.
Bankruptcy Court in  Manhattan .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Linda Sandler in New York at 
 lsandler@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Hytha at 
